@flexiarg structure/mana-allostasis
@title Mana Allostasis: Dissonance Is the Precursor to Resolution
@sigils [⚖️/熱]
@keywords mana, allostasis, balance, drain, award, dissonance, resolution, complexity, harmolodics
@audience mission operators, anyone watching their own metabolic state in the stack
@tone analytic-poetic
@factor Equanimity (upekkhā) — neither force closure nor over-extend the open block
@style pattern
@references [structure/block-as-futonic-revolution structure/cook-ting structure/hinge-point invariant-coherence/drain-channel-shape futon-theory/futonic-logic]

! conclusion: 
  The operator's metabolic state in the stack is the integral of
  (block-closures-at-hinges − allostatic-load-symptoms) over time.
  Block-closures award mana; allostatic-load symptoms drain it.
  The invariant is that net balance remains non-negative under
  sustained operation. Symptom channels are plural — working-tree
  dirt, mission-proliferation, session-sprawl, ahead-of-origin-
  without-disposition, untriaged-evidence — but they share a shape
  and an antidote: **perceive the hinge, close the block**.

  + context:
    Allostasis is the cumulative cost of physiological adaptation
    to stressors. It is not a defect — it is the theoretical
    precursor to resolution. Dissonance in music is not noise; it is
    the structure that gives consonance its meaning. In a futon
    stack, allostatic load is the rising tension that makes block-
    closure satisfying and noticeable. Without load, closure is
    unmotivated; without closure, load becomes degradation.

    Complexity, similarly, is not a fault to be minimised. A working
    tree in flux is the right state to be in *while doing the work*.
    What the invariant guards is not the absence of complexity but
    the timely return to a state where the substrate's transactional
    discipline holds.

  + IF:
    The operator is operating a futon stack with pluri-channel work
    (working trees, missions, sessions, branches, evidence streams),
    and is at risk of either (a) accumulating load past the point of
    coherent resolution, or (b) discharging load prematurely into
    rubber-stamp closures.

  + HOWEVER:
    No single channel is the whole story. Working-tree dirtiness is
    one symptom-channel; mission-proliferation is another; session-
    sprawl is another. Each drains by its own dynamic. Aggregating
    them into a single "you're tired" signal preserves the felt
    sense; separating them allows targeted resolution. Both readings
    are needed.

    Equally: not every block can or should close immediately.
    Some load is the *passion* phase of a block in flight — the
    operator is doing the actual work that the block will record.
    Pressure is welcome there; the invariant is not "minimise
    pressure" but "perceive when pressure becomes overdue."

    + ANTI-PATTERNS:
      - **Automation-of-closure**: forcing block-closure on a timer.
        Resolves dissonance without it being earned; produces hollow
        consonance. (jj-style; rubber-stamp commits.)
      - **Single-channel obsession**: tracking only working-tree
        pressure while letting mission-proliferation accumulate
        quietly. Drain is multi-channel; perception must be too.
      - **Mana-hoarding**: closing blocks for the award without the
        work. Each block-closure must rest on actual passion;
        otherwise the award is counterfeit, the system's metabolic
        sense miscalibrates, and real load goes unflagged.
      - **Dissonance-aversion**: forcing premature consonance. The
        operator commits to "feel done" rather than because the work
        is done. Music-theoretically: trite.
      - **Dissonance-luxuriance**: holding load indefinitely
        because "the work isn't ready." At some point dissonance
        becomes noise; the block must close even if imperfectly,
        then the next block can refine.

  + THEN:
    Track the per-channel drain rate. Surface to the operator when
    a channel approaches hinge-cadence overdue. Award mana at block-
    closure-at-recognised-hinge (only with the passion phase
    completed). Visualise the balance trajectory so the operator
    can see whether the system is accumulating or recovering.
    Distinguish "open block in passion" from "open block past
    hinge-cadence."

    + DIAGNOSTIC:
      - Many open missions, many open sessions, dirty working trees:
        multi-channel drain. Operator likely feels tired; confirm via
        proprioceptive check. Targeted hinge-perception, channel by
        channel.
      - All channels low, blocks closing regularly: net mana positive;
        the system is in healthy oscillation.
      - One channel pinned high, others quiet: targeted resolution is
        called for — perceive the specific hinge that's overdue and
        slip the blade.
      - Mana awards landing without prior load: counterfeit. Closures
        are happening without real work. Investigate (the awards may
        be from the wrong phase — e.g., closing a block before the
        passion phase has run).
      - Operator reports tiredness but futon-sync looks clean: the
        drain may be coming from a channel not currently measured
        (untriaged-evidence, attention-on-too-many-PRs, etc.).
        Widen the drain-channel inventory.

    + ON-DISSONANCE-AS-PRECURSOR:
      Consonance without prior dissonance is unmoving. A block-closure
      without prior accumulation is a non-event. The pressure function
      does not say "minimise load"; it says: when load approaches the
      natural resolution-point (a hinge), the operator should perceive
      it and act. The pleasure of the resolution scales with the load
      that preceded it. This is one reason cleanup blocks (after a
      long open passage) feel satisfying in a way that a hundred
      half-formed commits cannot.

    + ON-PASSION-AS-A-PHASE:
      The five-phase block lifecycle (identification → specification →
      elaboration → passion → closure; structure/block-as-futonic-
      revolution) names *passion* explicitly. This is the embodied-
      effort phase — where adenosine actually accumulates, where work
      actually gets done. Without naming this phase, the model would
      suggest that closure happens through pure perception. Real
      work has cost; the cost is the precondition for real
      resolution.

    + ON-PLURI-CHANNEL-HARMOLODICS:
      Working-tree dirt, mission-proliferation, session-sprawl,
      branch-bloat, untriaged-evidence — each a voice in a multi-
      voice composition. Harmolodics (Ornette Coleman) holds that
      harmony, melody, and rhythm are equally weighted; no single
      line dominates. The futonic invariant family has the same
      structure. Watching only one drain (e.g., working-tree
      dirtiness) while the others accumulate is monophonic
      listening.

    + REFERENCES:
      - structure/block-as-futonic-revolution — defines the unit that awards mana on close.
      - structure/cook-ting — the hinge-recognition that makes the close effortless.
      - structure/hinge-point — the structural slot where a hinge appears.
      - invariant-coherence/drain-channel-shape — how multiple bounded-disposition siblings share the drain-channel shape.
      - futon-theory/futonic-logic — the recognition loop the closure traverses.

  + BECAUSE:
    Sleep pressure is real. Music-theoretically, dissonance held
    too long without resolution becomes noise; resolved too early,
    music becomes trite. The same in stacks: allostatic load held
    too long without block-closure becomes substrate corruption
    (the M-live-geometric-stack manifold can't read it; agents and
    other operators see stale state). Resolved too early, blocks
    become hollow — work is "committed" without being done. The
    mana economy is the felt-sense interface to that physical
    reality.
